    "body": "I think all the gossip verification conditions are already satisfied!\r\n\r\n> If the execution is enabled for the block -- i.e. is_execution_enabled(state, block.body) then validate the following:\r\n[REJECT] The block's execution payload timestamp is correct with respect to the slot -- i.e. execution_payload.timestamp == compute_timestamp_at_slot(state, block.slot).\r\n\r\nCovered by:\r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/696de58141ecc34010c22256efac9c07849e5fb0/beacon_node/beacon_chain/src/execution_payload.rs#L178-L194\r\n\r\n\r\n> If exection_payload verification of block's parent by an execution node is not complete:\r\n[REJECT] The block's parent (defined by block.parent_root) passes all validation (excluding execution node verification of the block.body.execution_payload).\r\notherwise:\r\n[IGNORE] The block's parent (defined by block.parent_root) passes all validation (including execution node verification of the block.body.execution_payload).\r\n\r\nHere, the `parent_block` wouldn't be added to fork choice if it did not pass validation which covers both the cases.\r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/696de58141ecc34010c22256efac9c07849e5fb0/beacon_node/beacon_chain/src/execution_payload.rs#L163-L176\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n> The following gossip validation from prior specifications MUST NOT be applied if the execution is enabled for the block -- i.e. is_execution_enabled(state, block.body):\r\n[REJECT] The block's parent (defined by block.parent_root) passes validation.\r\n\r\nThis also seems to be satisfied as we add the parent block to fork choice with `ExecutionStatus::Unknown` if the execution status is unknown.\r\n\r\nTL;DR: I think this issue can be closed as we already pass all gossip verification conditions.",
